column1: #Text=Team DETR: Guide Queries as a Professional Team in Detection Transformers
#Text=> Authors: Tian Qiu, Linyun Zhou, Wenxiang Xu, Lechao Cheng, Zunlei Feng, Mingli Song
#Text=Recent proposed DETR variants have made tremendous progress in various scenarios due to their streamlined processes and
#Text=However, the learned queries usually explore the global context to generate the final set
#Text=prediction, resulting in redundant burdens and unfaithful results.
#Text=More specifically, a query is commonly responsible
#Text=for objects of different scales and positions, which is a challenge for the query itself, and will cause spatial
#Text=To alleviate this issue, we propose Team DETR, which leverages query collaboration
#Text=and position constraints to embrace objects of interest more precisely.
#Text=We also dynamically cater to each query member's
#Text=prediction preference, offering the query better scale and spatial priors.
#Text=In addition, the proposed Team DETR is
#Text=flexible enough to be adapted to other existing DETR variants without increasing parameters and calculations.
#Text=experiments on the COCO dataset show that Team DETR achieves remarkable gains, especially for small and large objects.
#Text=The proposed Team DETR is based on the basic architecture of DAB-DETR.
#Text=The CNN backbone is used to extract image
#Text=features, which are then fused by the transformer encoder.
#Text=The decoder utilizes several learned queries to match objects
#Text=A query is represented as an anchor box (x, y, w, h) and is dynamically updated based on the
#Text=offset (Δx, Δy, Δw, Δh) predicted by each decoder layer.
#Text=Building upon this, we introduce a query teamwork approach in
#Text=which the queries are grouped, and each group is responsible for objects within a specific scale range.
#Text=resource competition, the management area of each query is limited.
#Text=query are dynamically extracted, and the anchor is updated accordingly.
#Text=Without increasing parameters and calculations, our query teamwork can be easily integrated into DAB-based DETRs,
#Text=including DAB-DETR, DN-DETR and the single-stage DINO.

#Text=paper because we lost this checkpoint, and here is the one we retrained.
#Text=Our code contains three projects, Team-DAB-DETR, Team-DN-DETR, and Team-DINO, based on DAB-DETR, DN-DETR, and DINO,
#Text=respectively, and no extra dependency is needed.
#Text=So each of our projects can be installed the same way as its codebase.
#Text=[COCO2017](https://cocodataset.org/) is used to validate our method.

#Text=## How to integrate query teamwork into your model
#Text=The query teamwork contains three parts: scale-wise grouping, position constraint, and preference extraction.
#Text=For details, you can refer to our code.
#Text=Based on the source code of DAB-DETR / DN-DETR / DINO, every change in our code
#Text=The changes involve main.py, [DABDETR.py,] *transformer.py, matcher.py and engine.py.
#Text=Our Team DETR is based on the basic architecture of DAB-DETR and is flexible enough to be adapted to DAB-based DETRs:
